main event: A report from Project 10073 dating back to April 1957 mentions an unspecified aircraft at Phoenix, Arizona.
interesting points: The Air Force considers all information about flying saucers to be classified., There is significant public interest and criticism regarding the Air Force's handling of Project Blue Book information., An airliner reportedly struck 'something' 50 miles north of Phoenix around the same time., The report is a correspondence regarding the need for better public communication on UFO sightings., No photographs were present in the document.
